Description: Shoulder sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; exterior, white slip: on shoulder, palmette filling of lotus flower; below, two narrow bands and part of a maeander and square frieze.
Curator's comments: Cook (CVA BM 8, 8 no. 4) puts this sherd with British Museum 1924,1201.1053 and 1949,0516.18, and possibly with British Museum 1888.0601.556.b, 1888,0601.556.c (the findspot for this sherd is specified as the Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi) and British Museum 1949.0516.16. The modern inscription on the interior in ink 'NA123b' is a Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology accession number.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (p. 8, no. 4a, pl. 8, no. 4a)
